# Frontend — frontend_rules.md

## Purpose
Guidelines for building a readable, maintainable, accessible, and high-performance frontend for GuruPix.

---

## Goals
- Reusable components.
- Predictable state management.
- Accessibility-first approach.
- Strong typing with TypeScript.
- Performance and clean UX.

---

## Project Structure (Example)

/frontend
  /src
    /components
    /features
    /pages
    /hooks
    /services
    /styles
    /utils
    /assets
    /tests
  package.json
  tsconfig.json

---

## Coding Standards
- TypeScript with strict mode.
- Functional components + hooks.
- One component per file.
- ESLint + Prettier enforced in CI.

---

## State & Data
- React Query (or SWR) for server state.
- Local state kept close to usage.
- Typed API clients (OpenAPI or similar).

---

## Styling
- Tailwind CSS or CSS Modules.
- Use design tokens.
- Avoid global CSS pollution.

---

## Testing
- Unit tests: Jest + React Testing Library.
- E2E: Playwright or Cypress.
- Optional visual regression with Storybook.

---

## Performance
- Code splitting and lazy loading.
- Optimize images (webp/avif).
- Lighthouse checks in CI.

---

## Accessibility
- Semantic HTML.
- Keyboard navigation support.
- WCAG 2.1 AA contrast compliance.

---

## Developer Experience
- npm run dev
- npm run test
- .env.example provided
- Mock API option for local development

---

## Code Review Checklist
- Component tested?
- Accessible?
- Handles loading/error states?
- No unnecessary re-renders?

